descriptions.fix:
Configure the library files to be protected from unauthorized access. Run
the following command:

    $ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib -perm /022 -type f -exec chmod 755 '{}' \;

Configure the shared library directories to be protected from unauthorized
access. Run the following command:

    $ sudo find /lib /lib64 /usr/lib -perm /022 -type d -exec chmod 755 '{}' \;

Configure APT to remove all software components after updated versions have
been installed.

    Add or updated the following options to the
"/etc/apt/apt.conf.d/50unattended-upgrades" file:

    Unattended-Upgrade::Remove-Unused-Dependencies "true";
    Unattended-Upgrade::Remove-Unused-Kernel-Packages "true";
